n><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">It should also be noted that</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">, by around 2007,</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">more </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">schools with modest levels of disadvantage </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">were becoming</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> academies</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">, and the</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> prior </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">(KS2) </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">attainment </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">of academy entrants was rising towards the</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> national </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">average</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">.  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">My own </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">research</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">: emerging problems</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">17</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">) </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Drawing on official data, </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">my research has</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">scrutinised</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">attainment figures</span><spa